Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the noodles.

Pop the @diced chicken breast{260%g} in a #mixing bowl{}. Sprinkle over the @Chinese five spice{1/4%tsp} (careful not to use it all, it's quite strong!), and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well to coat the chicken, cover and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim the @green beans{80%g} then chop into thirds.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} into half moons.

Trim the @spring onion{2} and thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1/2}(peeled and grated) and @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Add the @egg noodle nests{2} to the pan of boiling water. Stir to separate, then cook for ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, then run under cold water until they lose their heat. Pop them back in their pan, fill with cold water and set aside.

While the noodles are cooking, heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} (or #wok{}) over high heat. Stir-fry the chicken until browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Tip: If necessary, cook the chicken in batches to make sure the meat doesn't stew.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a #bowl{} and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add another splash of @oil{} to your now empty pan (if it's dry) and lower the heat slightly. Add the pepper and green beans and stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the red onion and cook for another ~{2%minutes}, then add the chicken back into the pan.

Add the ginger and garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Drain the noodles and add them to the pan along with the @soy sauce{25%g}, @hoisin sauce{50%g} and a splash of @water{} to loosen.

Toss well, to make sure all the ingredients are combined and cook for another ~{2%minutes} to ensure the noodles are piping hot.

Finish the stir-fry by adding the spring onion and as much coriander as you like, then serve immediately. Enjoy!